<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">reached or heard at field meetings, they weakened <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">heir hands. It encouraged the Prelates and rulers <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">o proceed with an high hand, in their apo&s;tacy and <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">er&s;ecution. It will tempt po&s;terity to &s;ubmit to magi&s;trates' impo&s;ition of mini&s;ters, in what manner, <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">nd under what re&s;trictions they plea&s;e. It will <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">rieve and &s;tumble our Prote&s;tant brethren abroad, <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">o under&s;tand, that after all the faithful contendings <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">f Scotch mini&s;ters, from the Reformation till now, <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">o many, after a &s;hort &s;truggle, have &s;o fearfully com|<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">lied upon a &s;mall temptation.</P>
